  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> An enemy within 30 feet rolls a NAT 20 on an attack to you or an ally within 30 feet</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Your good fortune manifests itself in the failure of your foes. As a reaction, you can cause a creature within 30 feet to roll a will save against your class DC. This reaction has the misfortune trait. Once you have used this feature, you cannot do so again for 10 minutes.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The target is unaffected</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The triggering attack suffers a -2 circumstance penalty</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The target must reroll the natural 20 on a d20 roll and take the worse result.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The target's attempted roll is resolved as a NAT 1</p>"
    },
